%N A393721 The smallest number k such that the digit reversals of k, when written in all bases 2 to n, are less than k.
%H A393721 Scott R. Shannon, <a href="/A393721/b393721.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..45</a>
%F A393721 a(n) >= a(n-1).
%e A393721 a(6) = 60 as 60 = 111100_2 = 2020_3 = 330_4 = 220_5 = 140_6 whose digit reversals are 1111_2 = 15, 202_3 = 20, 33_4 = 15, 22_5 = 12, 41_6 = 25, all of which are less than 60.
%e A393721 a(10) = 1080. See A393902.
%t A393721 a[n_]:=Module[{k=1},While[!AllTrue[IntegerReverse[k,Range[2,n]],#<k&],k++];k];Array[a,17,2] (* _James C. McMahon_, Mar 04 2026 *)
%Y A393721 Cf. A393720, A393717, A393718, A393902, A393903, A305989, A305877, A004086.
%K A393721 nonn,base
%O A393721 2,1
